The paper discusses recovery guarantees for low-rank tensor recovery using models that minimize the trace norm and Frobenius norm of the tensor. This is a problem that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures (cs.DS), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). However, given that the paper focuses on optimization and guarantees, cs.IT and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CV, cs.DS, and cs.NA.
